content.description: weird hard sit start just right of lowball roof problem and barely left of the finger crack... but going straight up obvious shallow pockets. Right hand start on wierd undercling flake that is a bit hollow. Move up to small pockets and straight up.

start low and cramped on choss under roof. Mave move out to stellar sponge pinches then a hard drop knee move to a shallow two finger pocket. Really good rock quality after the first move. On par with Priest draw quality.
obvious finger crack just right of the obvious low ball roof problem.

pathTokens: Rowe well Road and Bright Angel Wash

content.description: Obvious (just visible from the road) small cluster of limestone boulders on the right side of the road A few miles down Rowe Well Rd past the kennels on your right. The boulder cluster is just visible when you cross over the train tracks as you head away from the village. Some good rock here but mostly short. There are a few good climbs, unfortunately the longer problems and best rock is withing 100 ft of a Rock Art Panel. I did not develop these and have left them untouched. There are three lines on the far left side I did develop which were just far enough out from the art to climb on. 1 finger crack (very short but fun) about v3ish. 1 really good roof problem about v6 ish... and 1 short contrived pocket problem with a low start at about v 6ish.
